  "text": "With the policy of quantitative easing newly ascendant, economists leaped to a variety of conclusions. Some argued that even if the monetary base were increased, its conversion into money supply would be gradual in a depressed economy, thus preventing uncontrollable inflation [CITATION_1] . Others were less sanguine about the impacts of quantitative easing.",
